node.text:
It’s a true wine spectacle! The Wine Room at @brennansnola reflects the glory of 75 years, 15,000 bottles, and a 16' slab of cypress which is located in the original carriage house and stable of the property. The historic 1795 building, designed by Edgar Degas’ grandfather has housed Brennan's since 1956 boasts a series of glamorous dining rooms, each resplendent with distinctive character, opulence, and whimsy.  And in the “cool” cellar, The Wine Room is a destination all its own. I spend a lot of time here, and you can see why! 

Follow along as I share a never- before- seen glimpse of our secret stash of rare spirits and vintages!

node.text: A decanter lets wines express themselves, separating the sediment that gathers at the bottom of aged wines and enhancing a wine’s flavors and aroma by exposing it to air. We asked our sommelier friend @barbara_somm to try out the Luigi Bormioli Crystal Crescendo Decanter and asked her why she decants. “We aerate wine so we can enjoy the wine at its height, in all its glory,” she says. “I compare it to allowing a rose time to open all of its petals so we can appreciate it in all of its beauty before its natural decline.” Check out our new shop—and all our wine tools—through the button in our profile.

node.text: In our continued mission to introduce you to the best bar tools, glassware, and more, we bring you the Bad Ass Plastic Muddler. The ingredients that see the business end of a muddler include just about any ingredient whose flavor you want to impart into your drink. Top of the list this summer? Strawberries. So, we asked our collaborator and bar pro @professor.baker to make a sophisticated Strawberry Daiquiri to try out the muddler and few other select tools, as part of our ongoing celebration of the new Liquor.com Store! Check out the full line thru the “View Shop” button in our profile.

Inspired by the harvest season in late September, the aptly named Harvest Moon by Shawn Chen, the beverage director at RedFarm and Decoy, embodies fall’s coziest flavors. Bonus: a garnish of Concord grapes soaked in pomegranate molasses brandy and rolled in crushed almond pieces. Recipe in bio link. #newclassics

node.text: Master the art of making bar-quality cocktails at home with our Cocktail Kit! Our friend @professor.baker put it through its paces with a Tom Collins variation, using cucumber-infused ice cubes molded from the Cocktail Kingdom 1.25-Inch Square Ice Cube Tray. “The tray is perfect for the home bartender, especially since no one keeps a Kold Draft ice machine in their house!” says Baker. “This mold makes ice that is very solid, perfect particularly for spirit-forward cocktails.” Check out the full store through the “View Shop” button in our profile.

node.text:
A purl is an old-school English drink classically involving hot ale. It can be served with or without warming spices and a nice dollop of gin. In the Golden Purl from Denver-based writer Linnea Covington, the ale is replaced with warm sparkling cider. The fizzy apple cider adds refreshing effervescence to the drink and works well with the dry gin and the sweet, bourbon barrel-aged maple syrup, which brings a hefty, buttery quality to the mix. Recipe in bio link.

node.text: To celebrate the opening of the Liquor.com store, we had some pros test drive the gear. Our friend and frequent collaborator @professor.baker decided to use the techniques required to make a classic Manhattan, to put the equipment properly to the test. The result? He was more than pleased—especially with the Crafthouse Jigger: “I absolutely love this jigger…it has a spout on it, which is extremely helpful for not making a mess when pouring!” he says. “I think it will raise the standard for all jiggers entering the market.” Check out all the tools used in the video through the “View Shop” button in our profile.
